A RESOLUTION
1 Supporting the Ray City Community Library's membership in state-supported public library
2 services; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, the City of Ray City anticipates that funding opportunities for local facilities
4 will be available under President Donald Trump to Expand Educational Freedom and
5 Opportunities for Families; and
6 WHEREAS, the Ray City Community Library has long been a vital community resource,
7 operated by the municipality for over 20 years as a municipal library without support from
8 the State of Georgia via the Georgia Public Library Service, a unit of the Board of Regents
9 of the University System of Georgia; and
10 WHEREAS, citizens have benefited from the library's dedicated support of numerous
11 community volunteers who have contributed their time and talents to its operation; and
12 WHEREAS, state support as provided by the Georgia Public Library Service is a necessary
13 prerequisite for the Ray City Community Library to access valuable library services,
14 including interlibrary loan programs, the PINES catalog, facilities planning, and professional
15 development opportunities; and
