16 WHEREAS, state support as provided by the Georgia Public Library Service is also essential
17 for the Ray City Community Library to be eligible for state and federal funding
18 opportunities, which will enable the library to update its facilities, services, collections, and
19 programs for the benefit of the community; and
20 WHEREAS, under O.C.G.A. § 20-2-305, the Board of Regents of the University System of
21 Georgia is authorized to distribute state and federal funds "to county and regional public
22 libraries in proportion to the area and population to be served by such libraries…all such
23 funds shall be distributed directly to the regional or county library boards"; and
24 WHEREAS, Ray City is located within Berrien County, which is a member of the Coastal
25 Plain Regional Library System.
26 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
27 express their strong support for the Ray City Community Library's membership in the
28 Coastal Plain Regional Library System in order to be eligible for support from the Georgia
29 Public Library Service.
30 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the members of this body recognize the significant
31 contributions of the Ray City Community Library to preserving the local heritage and
32 emphasize the importance of its continued growth and development.
33 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the members of this body urge the Board of Regents,
34 the Regents Public Library Advisory Committee, the Georgia State Library System, the
35 Regional Library Board, and the Berrien County Library Board to favorably consider the Ray
36 City Community Library's facility and grant it full membership in the Coastal Plain Regional
